documentType: court filing or evidence preparation record
summary: This document records an Assistant U.S. Attorney's preparation and review of evidence related to the October 20, 2005 search of Jeffrey Epstein's property. It confirms the authenticity of video discs from the search and a green massage table seized from the master bathroom, noting a faint white line recognized as semen.

persons.name: AUSA Det.
persons.context: The prosecutor who reviewed and confirmed the authenticity of evidence from the 2005 search, including video discs and a massage table.

connections.description: AUSA Det. reviewed evidence that El had seized and documented, confirming its accuracy and chain of custody.

events.title: Search of Epstein Property
events.description: Law enforcement executed a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's property, seizing video evidence and a green massage table from the men's master bathroom.

events.title: Evidence Review and Authentication
events.description: An Assistant U.S. Attorney reviewed and authenticated evidence from the 2005 search, including video discs and the massage table, confirming their accuracy and chain of custody.

keyFacts: Video evidence (GX-296, GX-296R, GX-296RR) from the October 20, 2005 search was authenticated as accurate copies.
A green massage table (GX-51) was seized from the men's master bathroom during the 2005 search and confirmed to match property receipts.
The seizing officer (El) noted a faint white line on the massage table that he recognized as semen at the time of seizure.
The document is subject to a protective order restricting certain paragraphs, indicating sensitive or confidential information.
